<subSubSection pageId="80" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="80.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[666,866,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[666,790,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">A. nigripes</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
by having the clypeal carina higher than the frons [in profile]; the antennal flagellomeres serrate; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the circumocular suture absent; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle obtuse; and the mesopleuron with the anterior fovea longer than the posterior, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[250,373,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[250,373,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">A. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the clypeal carina lower than the frons [in profile]; the antennal flagellomeres filiform; the antennal scrobe carina distinct and reaching the eye; the circumocular suture present; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle acute; and the mesopleuron with the anterior fovea as long as the posterior.
</paragraph>
